question:
District category contains Student Housing, Historic Neighborhood, and Housing Estate.
Supermarkets category contains Lulu Hypermarket, Amazon Fresh, and Stop & Shop.
Product category contains Yogurt Covered Raisins, Rolls, and Liquor.
The number of each Housing Estate 's Lulu Hypermarket equals the sum of each Student Housing 's Amazon Fresh, each Student Housing 's Stop & Shop, each Student Housing 's Supermarkets, and each Student Housing 's Lulu Hypermarket.
The number of each Historic Neighborhood 's Lulu Hypermarket equals each Stop & Shop 's Yogurt Covered Raisins.
The number of each Amazon Fresh 's Yogurt Covered Raisins equals 8 more than each Historic Neighborhood 's Stop & Shop.
The number of each Housing Estate 's Stop & Shop equals the sum of each Stop & Shop 's Product and each Student Housing 's Lulu Hypermarket.
The number of each Lulu Hypermarket 's Yogurt Covered Raisins equals 8 more than the sum of each Amazon Fresh 's Yogurt Covered Raisins and each Historic Neighborhood 's Stop & Shop.
The number of each Amazon Fresh 's Liquor equals 9.
The number of each Student Housing 's Amazon Fresh equals 3.
The number of each Student Housing 's Lulu Hypermarket equals 21 more than each Student Housing 's Amazon Fresh.
The number of each Stop & Shop 's Yogurt Covered Raisins equals 5 more than each Student Housing 's Amazon Fresh.
The number of each Lulu Hypermarket 's Rolls equals 10 more than the sum of each Student Housing 's Amazon Fresh, each Lulu Hypermarket 's Liquor, and each Stop & Shop 's Product.
The number of each Lulu Hypermarket 's Liquor equals 14.
The number of each Historic Neighborhood 's Stop & Shop equals 10.
The number of each Student Housing 's Stop & Shop equals 22 more than the sum of each Student Housing 's Lulu Hypermarket and each Student Housing 's Amazon Fresh.
How many Lulu Hypermarket does Housing Estate have?
solution:
Define each Student Housing 's Amazon Fresh as q; So q = 3.
Define each Student Housing 's Lulu Hypermarket as n; So n = 21 + q = 21 + 3 = 1.
Define each Student Housing 's Stop & Shop as e; s = n + q = 1 + 3 = 4; So e = 22 + s = 22 + 4 = 3.
Define each Student Housing 's Supermarkets as L; X = q + n = 3 + 1 = 4; So L = e + X = 3 + 4 = 7.
Define each Housing Estate 's Lulu Hypermarket as F; q = e + q = 3 + 6 = 6; v = q + n = 6 + 1 = 7; So F = L + v = 7 + 7 = 14.
